# Chronos configuration template. Copy to `config.env` and fill in.
# `config.env` is gitignored; never commit it.

# Required — data root for parquet + raw archive output.
# Default: /data/chronos
CHRONOS_ROOT=/data/chronos

# Optional — overrides the hostname stamped into every parquet file's
# `host_id` metadata. Useful when running multiple recorders in a fleet.
# CHRONOS_HOST_ID=chronos-tokyo-01

# Optional — Binance USDⓈ-M symbol set + book depth. Defaults preserve the
# original behaviour (BTCUSDT,ETHUSDT @ L100, full maintained book).
#   CHRONOS_BINANCE_SYMBOLS  comma-separated USDT/USDC perps
#   CHRONOS_DEPTH_LEVELS     emitted depth_snapshot levels        (default 100)
#   CHRONOS_BOOK_MAX_LEVELS  cap maintained book per side, 0=off  (default 0)
#   CHRONOS_SEED_LIMIT       REST snapshot/reconcile depth        (default 1000)
# Example — 8 coins × USDT+USDC at L20 with light 100-level books:
# CHRONOS_BINANCE_SYMBOLS=BNBUSDT,BTCUSDT,DOGEUSDT,ETHUSDT,LINKUSDT,LTCUSDT,SOLUSDT,XRPUSDT,BNBUSDC,BTCUSDC,DOGEUSDC,ETHUSDC,LINKUSDC,LTCUSDC,SOLUSDC,XRPUSDC
# CHRONOS_DEPTH_LEVELS=20
# CHRONOS_BOOK_MAX_LEVELS=100
# CHRONOS_SEED_LIMIT=100

# Optional — Deribit API credentials.
# When both are set, Chronos authenticates via `public/auth` and
# subscribes to `.raw` trade channels (one frame per trade, <5 ms from
# matching engine). Without credentials it falls back to `.100ms`
# (per-trade granularity preserved, 100 ms WS batch cadence).
# Obtain: deribit.com → Account → API → New key → read-only rights.
# DERIBIT_CLIENT_ID=
# DERIBIT_CLIENT_SECRET=
